"You don't know what you don't know, and it might be better than what you do" It's incredible how you can be so fearful of the world and it's unpredictability, vastness, and consequence in your day to day, yet the moment you set off on your bike, you yearn for those same things. You take risks, get lost and you strive for the consequence of that experience and all its unknowns.
